41 /*!
42  * \class CEmptyMap
43  * \brief We use this dummy class instead of std::map when
44  * we only need the enum definition and not the string to
45  * enum maps, this makes compilation much faster.
46  */
47 template <typename T, typename U>
48 struct CEmptyMap {
49  CEmptyMap(std::initializer_list<std::pair<const T, U> >) {}
50 };

155 /*!
156  * \brief Get the number of faces of the element.
157  * \param[in] elementType - element type
158  * \return number of faces
159  */
160 inline unsigned short nFacesOfElementType(unsigned short elementType) {
161  switch (elementType) {
162  case LINE: return N_FACES_LINE;
163  case TRIANGLE: return N_FACES_TRIANGLE;
164  case QUADRILATERAL: return N_FACES_QUADRILATERAL;
165  case TETRAHEDRON: return N_FACES_TETRAHEDRON;
166  case HEXAHEDRON: return N_FACES_HEXAHEDRON;
167  case PYRAMID: return N_FACES_PYRAMID;
168  case PRISM: return N_FACES_PRISM;
169  default: assert(false && "Invalid element type."); return 0;
170  }
171 }
172 
173 /*!
174  * \brief Get the number of points of the element.
175  * \param[in] elementType - element type
176  * \return number of points
177  */
178 inline unsigned short nPointsOfElementType(unsigned short elementType) {
179  switch (elementType) {
180  case LINE: return N_POINTS_LINE;
181  case TRIANGLE: return N_POINTS_TRIANGLE;
182  case QUADRILATERAL: return N_POINTS_QUADRILATERAL;
183  case TETRAHEDRON: return N_POINTS_TETRAHEDRON;
184  case HEXAHEDRON: return N_POINTS_HEXAHEDRON;
185  case PYRAMID: return N_POINTS_PYRAMID;
186  case PRISM: return N_POINTS_PRISM;
187  default: assert(false && "Invalid element type."); return 0;
188  }
189 }

996 /*!
997  * \brief Function to parse SST options.
998  * \param[in] SST_Options - Selected SST option from config.
999  * \param[in] nSST_Options - Number of options selected.
1000  * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1001  * \return Struct with SST options.
1002  */
1003 inline SST_ParsedOptions ParseSSTOptions(const SST_OPTIONS *SST_Options, unsigned short nSST_Options, int rank) {
1004  SST_ParsedOptions SSTParsedOptions;
1005 
1006  auto IsPresent = [&](SST_OPTIONS option) {
1007  const auto sst_options_end = SST_Options + nSST_Options;
1008  return std::find(SST_Options, sst_options_end, option) != sst_options_end;
1009  };
1010 
1011  const bool found_1994 = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V1994);
1012  const bool found_2003 = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V2003);
1013  const bool found_1994m = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V1994m);
1014  const bool found_2003m = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V2003m);
1015 
1016  const bool default_version = !found_1994 && !found_1994m && !found_2003 && !found_2003m;
1017 
1018  const bool sst_1994 = found_1994 || found_1994m || default_version;
1019  const bool sst_2003 = found_2003 || found_2003m;
1020 
1021  /*--- When V2003m or V1994m is selected, we automatically select sst_m. ---*/
1022  const bool sst_m = found_1994m || found_2003m || default_version;
1023 
1024  const bool sst_sust = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::SUST);
1025  const bool sst_v = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V);
1026  const bool sst_kl = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::KL);
1027  const bool sst_uq = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::UQ);
1028 
1029  if (sst_1994 && sst_2003) {
1030  SU2_MPI::Error("Two versions (1994 and 2003) selected for SST_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1031  } else if (sst_2003) {
1032  SSTParsedOptions.version = SST_OPTIONS::V2003;
1033  } else {
1034  SSTParsedOptions.version = SST_OPTIONS::V1994;
1035 
1036  if (rank==MASTER_NODE) {
1037  std::cout <<
1038  "WARNING: The current SST-1994m model is inconsistent with literature. We recommend using the SST-2003m model.\n"
1039  "In SU2 v8 the 2003m model will become default, and the inconsistency will be fixed." << std::endl;
1040  }
1041  }
1042 
1043  // Parse production modifications
1044  if ((int(sst_v) + int(sst_kl) + int(sst_uq)) > 1) {
1045  SU2_MPI::Error("Please select only one SST production term modifier (VORTICITY, KATO-LAUNDER, or UQ).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1046  } else if (sst_v) {
1047  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::V;
1048  } else if (sst_kl) {
1049  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::KL;
1050  } else if (sst_uq) {
1051  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::UQ;
1052  }
1053 
1054  SSTParsedOptions.sust = sst_sust;
1055  SSTParsedOptions.modified = sst_m;
1056  SSTParsedOptions.uq = sst_uq;
1057  return SSTParsedOptions;
1058 }

1098 /*!
1099  * \brief Function to parse SA options.
1100  * \param[in] SA_Options - Selected SA option from config.
1101  * \param[in] nSA_Options - Number of options selected.
1102  * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1103  * \return Struct with SA options.
1104  */
1105 inline SA_ParsedOptions ParseSAOptions(const SA_OPTIONS *SA_Options, unsigned short nSA_Options, int rank) {
1106  SA_ParsedOptions SAParsedOptions;
1107 
1108  auto IsPresent = [&](SA_OPTIONS option) {
1109  const auto sa_options_end = SA_Options + nSA_Options;
1110  return std::find(SA_Options, sa_options_end, option) != sa_options_end;
1111  };
1112 
1113  const bool found_neg = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::NEG);
1114  const bool found_edw = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::EDW);
1115  const bool found_bsl = !found_neg && !found_edw;
1116 
1117  if (found_neg && found_edw) {
1118  SU2_MPI::Error("Two versions (Negative and Edwards) selected for SA_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1119  }
1120 
1121  if (found_bsl) {
1122  SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::NONE;
1123  } else if (found_neg) {
1124  SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::NEG;
1125  } else {
1126  SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::EDW;
1127  }
1128  SAParsedOptions.ft2 = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::FT2);
1129  SAParsedOptions.qcr2000 = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::QCR2000);
1130  SAParsedOptions.comp = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::COMP);
1131  SAParsedOptions.rot = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::ROT);
1132  SAParsedOptions.bc = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::BC);
1133 
1134  /*--- Validate user settings when not in experimental mode. ---*/
1135  if (!IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::EXP)) {
1136  const bool any_but_bc = SAParsedOptions.ft2 || SAParsedOptions.qcr2000 || SAParsedOptions.comp || SAParsedOptions.rot;
1137 
1138  switch (SAParsedOptions.version) {
1139  case SA_OPTIONS::NEG:
1140  if (!SAParsedOptions.ft2 || SAParsedOptions.bc)
1141  SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-neg was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1142  "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1143  break;
1144  case SA_OPTIONS::EDW:
1145  if (any_but_bc || SAParsedOptions.bc)
1146  SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-noft2-Edwards was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1147  "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1148  break;
1149  default:
1150  if (SAParsedOptions.bc && any_but_bc)
1151  SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-BCM was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1152  "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1153  break;
1154  }
1155  }
1156  return SAParsedOptions;
1157 }

1222 /*!
1223  * \brief Function to parse LM options.
1224  * \param[in] LM_Options - Selected LM option from config.
1225  * \param[in] nLM_Options - Number of options selected.
1226  * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1227  * \return Struct with SA options.
1228  */
1229 inline LM_ParsedOptions ParseLMOptions(const LM_OPTIONS *LM_Options, unsigned short nLM_Options, int rank, TURB_MODEL Kind_Turb_Model) {
1230  LM_ParsedOptions LMParsedOptions;
1231 
1232  auto IsPresent = [&](LM_OPTIONS option) {
1233  const auto lm_options_end = LM_Options + nLM_Options;
1234  return std::find(LM_Options, lm_options_end, option) != lm_options_end;
1235  };
1236 
1237  LMParsedOptions.LM2015 = IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::LM2015);
1238 
1239  int NFoundCorrelations = 0;
1240  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MALAN)) {
1241  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN;
1242  NFoundCorrelations++;
1243  }
1244  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::SULUKSNA)) {
1245  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::SULUKSNA;
1246  NFoundCorrelations++;
1247  }
1248  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::KRAUSE)) {
1249  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE;
1250  NFoundCorrelations++;
1251  }
1252  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::KRAUSE_HYPER)) {
1253  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE_HYPER;
1254  NFoundCorrelations++;
1255  }
1256  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MEDIDA_BAEDER)) {
1257  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA_BAEDER;
1258  NFoundCorrelations++;
1259  }
1260  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MEDIDA)) {
1261  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA;
1262  NFoundCorrelations++;
1263  }
1264  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MENTER_LANGTRY)) {
1265  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY;
1266  NFoundCorrelations++;
1267  }
1268 
1269  if (NFoundCorrelations > 1) {
1270  SU2_MPI::Error("Two correlations selected for LM_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1271  }
1272 
1273  if (LMParsedOptions.Correlation == TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::DEFAULT){
1274  if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST) {
1275  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY;
1276  } else if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SA) {
1277  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN;
1278  }
1279  }
1280 
1281  return LMParsedOptions;
1282 }

2002 /*!
2003  * \brief Return true if format is one of the Paraview options.
2004  */
2005 inline bool isParaview(OUTPUT_TYPE format) {
2006  switch(format) {
2007  case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_ASCII:
2008  case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_LEGACY_BINARY:
2009  case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_ASCII:
2010  case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_LEGACY_BINARY:
2011  case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_XML:
2012  case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_XML:
2013  case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK:
2014  return true;
2015  default:
2016  return false;
2017  }
2018 }
